00:13:28.415 --> 00:13:29.790 align:middle line:84%
I think it is much
better to look

00:13:29.790 --> 00:13:33.510 align:middle line:84%
at diet as a way of maintaining
and enhancing health than just

00:13:33.510 --> 00:13:34.350 align:middle line:90%
about weight loss.

00:13:34.350 --> 00:13:35.940 align:middle line:84%
You lost half of the
audience right there.

00:13:35.940 --> 00:13:36.390 align:middle line:90%
>> Sorry.

00:13:36.390 --> 00:13:37.557 align:middle line:90%
>> They want to lose weight.

00:13:37.557 --> 00:13:42.810 align:middle line:84%
>> OK, I would recommend going
on a diet have 50% to 60%

00:13:42.810 --> 00:13:44.790 align:middle line:90%
of calories as carbohydrate.

00:13:44.790 --> 00:13:46.680 align:middle line:84%
And if you are
carbohydrate sensitive,

00:13:46.680 --> 00:13:50.302 align:middle line:84%
you want to pay particular
attention to the glycemic index

00:13:50.302 --> 00:13:52.260 align:middle line:84%
and to stay away from
these high-glycemic index

00:13:52.260 --> 00:13:53.320 align:middle line:90%
foods, all the fluffy stuff.

00:13:53.320 --> 00:13:54.210 align:middle line:90%
>> So those are--

00:13:54.210 --> 00:13:55.830 align:middle line:90%
high glycemic would be bread.

00:13:55.830 --> 00:13:58.102 align:middle line:84%
>> It's most-- a
lot of potatoes.

00:13:58.102 --> 00:13:59.310 align:middle line:90%
>> What about sweet potatoes?

00:13:59.310 --> 00:14:01.050 align:middle line:90%
>> Sweet potatoes are OK.

00:14:01.050 --> 00:14:04.000 align:middle line:84%
Even waxing new potatoes
are OK in moderation--

00:14:04.000 --> 00:14:06.160 align:middle line:84%
it's the flowery,
big flowery potatoes.

00:14:06.160 --> 00:14:07.530 align:middle line:90%
>> The mashed potatoes.

00:14:07.530 --> 00:14:09.750 align:middle line:84%
>> You want to try to
stay away from white--

00:14:09.750 --> 00:14:11.580 align:middle line:84%
as many white flour
products as you

00:14:11.580 --> 00:14:15.450 align:middle line:84%
can and even whole wheat bread
that's essentially the same.

00:14:15.450 --> 00:14:18.090 align:middle line:90%
It's colored white bread.

00:14:18.090 --> 00:14:21.620 align:middle line:84%
I think you want to avoid
immoderate quantities of pasta.

00:14:21.620 --> 00:14:23.610 align:middle line:84%
You want to be
moderate about that.

00:14:23.610 --> 00:14:26.310 align:middle line:84%
In terms of rice,
Basmati rice is

00:14:26.310 --> 00:14:28.950 align:middle line:84%
better than sticky,
Chinese or Japanese rice.

00:14:28.950 --> 00:14:30.240 align:middle line:90%
>> That was interesting to me.

00:14:30.240 --> 00:14:32.220 align:middle line:84%
>> Interesting to know
about that, right.

00:14:32.220 --> 00:14:34.230 align:middle line:90%
But that's basic information.

00:14:34.230 --> 00:14:37.350 align:middle line:84%
I would also say that you
want to eat about 10% to 20%

00:14:37.350 --> 00:14:39.120 align:middle line:90%
of calories as protein.

00:14:39.120 --> 00:14:41.790 align:middle line:84%
And I'd recommend that, as
much as possible, of that

00:14:41.790 --> 00:14:44.490 align:middle line:84%
be fish and vegetable
protein because this

00:14:44.490 --> 00:14:46.770 align:middle line:90%
has healthful elements in it.

00:14:46.770 --> 00:14:49.030 align:middle line:84%
And soy products
are right in there.

00:14:49.030 --> 00:14:51.480 align:middle line:84%
And then I would say that
you can have 25% to 30%

00:14:51.480 --> 00:14:53.070 align:middle line:90%
of calories as fat.

00:14:53.070 --> 00:14:55.980 align:middle line:84%
And my recommendation is your
principle fat the olive oil

00:14:55.980 --> 00:14:58.350 align:middle line:84%
and that you make a great
effort to increase consumption

00:14:58.350 --> 00:15:03.060 align:middle line:84%
of omega-3 fatty acids by eating
fish like salmon or sardines

00:15:03.060 --> 00:15:08.220 align:middle line:84%
or herring or walnuts or
flax seeds or soy products,

00:15:08.220 --> 00:15:10.220 align:middle line:90%
which give you some of it.

00:15:10.220 --> 00:15:14.095 align:middle line:84%
>> But you kind of
limit, in your book,

00:15:14.095 --> 00:15:17.320 align:middle line:84%
the fish that we can eat
because you say so much of it is

00:15:17.320 --> 00:15:18.250 align:middle line:90%
contaminated.

00:15:18.250 --> 00:15:19.390 align:middle line:90%
>> Well, this is a problem.

00:15:19.390 --> 00:15:21.760 align:middle line:84%
And I think that you
know some fish are

00:15:21.760 --> 00:15:23.080 align:middle line:90%
more of a danger than others.

00:15:23.080 --> 00:15:24.578 align:middle line:90%
I would not eat swordfish.

00:15:24.578 --> 00:15:26.620 align:middle line:84%
It's too big, and it's
too carnivorous and likely

00:15:26.620 --> 00:15:28.660 align:middle line:90%
to concentrate toxins.

00:15:28.660 --> 00:15:30.260 align:middle line:90%
Sardines I think are OK.

00:15:30.260 --> 00:15:31.780 align:middle line:84%
They're a little
fish, and they're

00:15:31.780 --> 00:15:33.700 align:middle line:90%
a good source of omega-3s.

00:15:33.700 --> 00:15:35.500 align:middle line:90%
>> Why is a big fish--

00:15:35.500 --> 00:15:38.530 align:middle line:84%
>> The bigger the fish and
the more carnivorous it is,

00:15:38.530 --> 00:15:41.410 align:middle line:84%
the more it's at the
top of its food chain,

00:15:41.410 --> 00:15:44.380 align:middle line:84%
and the more it accumulates
all the toxins at every level

00:15:44.380 --> 00:15:47.380 align:middle line:84%
of this chain by which
smaller things, which--

00:15:47.380 --> 00:15:48.802 align:middle line:90%
bigger things eats more things.

00:15:48.802 --> 00:15:50.260 align:middle line:84%
>> And yet, you
say salmon is good.

00:15:50.260 --> 00:15:51.310 align:middle line:90%
That's a pretty big fish.

00:15:51.310 --> 00:15:52.602 align:middle line:90%
>> Salmon is a pretty big fish.

00:15:52.602 --> 00:15:56.030 align:middle line:84%
It's probably in the middle
range in terms of toxicity.

00:15:56.030 --> 00:15:57.760 align:middle line:84%
Most of the salmon
we get now is farmed.

00:15:57.760 --> 00:16:00.800 align:middle line:84%
It's possible to farm
salmon in clean water.

00:16:00.800 --> 00:16:04.300 align:middle line:84%
I have seen some organic farmed
salmon available in which drugs

00:16:04.300 --> 00:16:06.280 align:middle line:90%
are not used, like antibiotics.

00:16:06.280 --> 00:16:08.800 align:middle line:84%
The problem is that
much farmed salmon

00:16:08.800 --> 00:16:11.440 align:middle line:84%
has a lower omega-3
content than wild salmon,

00:16:11.440 --> 00:16:12.820 align:middle line:84%
but that could
easily be adjusted

00:16:12.820 --> 00:16:14.290 align:middle line:90%
by what you feed the salmon.

00:16:14.290 --> 00:16:15.970 align:middle line:84%
And it would be great
if people started

00:16:15.970 --> 00:16:19.010 align:middle line:84%
making high omega-3 farmed
salmon that was clean--

00:16:19.010 --> 00:16:20.257 align:middle line:90%
could easily happen.

00:16:20.257 --> 00:16:21.590 align:middle line:90%
There's a new egg on the market.

00:16:21.590 --> 00:16:23.290 align:middle line:84%
These are high omega-3
eggs that have--

00:16:23.290 --> 00:16:24.790 align:middle line:84%
>> Yeah I bought
some the other day.

00:16:24.790 --> 00:16:26.590 align:middle line:84%
>> They taste good,
and they're good.

00:16:26.590 --> 00:16:26.950 align:middle line:90%
So this is another good source--

00:16:26.950 --> 00:16:27.840 align:middle line:90%
>> --and mild.

00:16:27.840 --> 00:16:31.362 align:middle line:84%
>> Yeah this is another good
source of omega-3 fatty acids.

00:16:31.362 --> 00:16:33.180 align:middle line:90%
>> Now, I read your book.

00:16:33.180 --> 00:16:36.690 align:middle line:84%
Since I first met you,
I now put my olive oil

00:16:36.690 --> 00:16:37.900 align:middle line:90%
in the refrigerator.

00:16:37.900 --> 00:16:38.850 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, right.

00:16:38.850 --> 00:16:40.790 align:middle line:84%
You know, it's OK to
leave a little bit out

00:16:40.790 --> 00:16:43.290 align:middle line:84%
except in the real hot time of
year because it's convenient.

00:16:43.290 --> 00:16:46.460 align:middle line:84%
But I think you don't want to
buy oils in big quantities.

00:16:46.460 --> 00:16:49.150 align:middle line:84%
Keep them in the refrigerator
because it retards oxidation,

00:16:49.150 --> 00:16:50.340 align:middle line:90%
which is much healthier.

00:16:50.340 --> 00:16:51.840 align:middle line:84%
And of course, you
want to be eating

00:16:51.840 --> 00:16:54.390 align:middle line:84%
plenty of fruits and vegetables
of good quality on any diet.

00:16:54.390 --> 00:16:56.160 align:middle line:90%
>> All right, what about--

00:16:56.160 --> 00:17:01.380 align:middle line:84%
let's talk about nitty-gritty
here, Haagen-Dazs ice cream?

00:17:01.380 --> 00:17:02.835 align:middle line:90%
How terrible is it?

00:17:02.835 --> 00:17:06.480 align:middle line:90%
>> Well, it is--

00:17:06.480 --> 00:17:09.250 align:middle line:84%
a little bit now and
then it's probably OK.

00:17:09.250 --> 00:17:12.990 align:middle line:84%
But in some ways,
maybe it's even better

00:17:12.990 --> 00:17:14.369 align:middle line:90%
than low-fat frozen yogurt.

00:17:14.369 --> 00:17:16.260 align:middle line:84%
Because the low-fat
frozen yogurt,

00:17:16.260 --> 00:17:19.180 align:middle line:84%
you've got more high glycemic
index carbohydrate calories

00:17:19.180 --> 00:17:19.980 align:middle line:90%
in it.

00:17:19.980 --> 00:17:23.010 align:middle line:84%
>> You say stay away from
everything that says no fat

00:17:23.010 --> 00:17:23.880 align:middle line:90%
or low fat.

00:17:23.880 --> 00:17:25.588 align:middle line:84%
>> I think-- we'll,
look what's happened.

00:17:25.588 --> 00:17:28.590 align:middle line:84%
As no fat and low fat foods have
become more and more prominent

00:17:28.590 --> 00:17:30.600 align:middle line:84%
in the American
marketplace, Americans

00:17:30.600 --> 00:17:32.220 align:middle line:90%
have steadily gotten fatter.

00:17:32.220 --> 00:17:33.990 align:middle line:84%
So something's wrong
with that picture.

00:17:33.990 --> 00:17:36.180 align:middle line:84%
And I think one of the
things is that people imagine

00:17:36.180 --> 00:17:38.970 align:middle line:84%
that you could eat these foods
with abandon, that they're

00:17:38.970 --> 00:17:40.140 align:middle line:90%
no-calorie foods.

00:17:40.140 --> 00:17:41.850 align:middle line:84%
And that certainly
is not the case.

00:17:41.850 --> 00:17:45.453 align:middle line:84%
And often, the low fat foods
have higher amounts of sugar

00:17:45.453 --> 00:17:47.370 align:middle line:84%
to make them taste better,
and that's probably

00:17:47.370 --> 00:17:50.540 align:middle line:84%
worse for people who are
carbohydrate sensitive.

00:17:50.540 --> 00:17:56.950 align:middle line:84%
>> So maybe we get more
satisfied with a food that has

00:17:56.950 --> 00:17:57.840 align:middle line:90%
a higher fat content.

00:17:57.840 --> 00:17:58.640 align:middle line:90%
>> I think so.

00:17:58.640 --> 00:18:01.520 align:middle line:84%
Fat is more satiating, and I
think that's one reason, again,

00:18:01.520 --> 00:18:05.480 align:middle line:84%
why the Atkins diet may work
for people because, when you're

00:18:05.480 --> 00:18:08.270 align:middle line:84%
eating high fat foods, you
have a sensation of fullness

00:18:08.270 --> 00:18:10.820 align:middle line:84%
and satisfaction quicker,
and you actually may end up

00:18:10.820 --> 00:18:12.770 align:middle line:90%
taking in fewer calories.

00:18:12.770 --> 00:18:15.020 align:middle line:84%
>> You also brought up the
point that it starts to get

00:18:15.020 --> 00:18:17.780 align:middle line:90%
so boring, boring.

00:18:17.780 --> 00:18:21.060 align:middle line:84%
>> Yeah, I said I think any
monotonous diet you will lose

00:18:21.060 --> 00:18:21.860 align:middle line:90%
weight on.

00:18:21.860 --> 00:18:23.900 align:middle line:84%
I said in the book
that I probably

00:18:23.900 --> 00:18:26.118 align:middle line:84%
could design an
all cheesecake diet

00:18:26.118 --> 00:18:28.160 align:middle line:84%
that you can have as much
cheesecake as you want,

00:18:28.160 --> 00:18:30.630 align:middle line:84%
but nothing but
cheesecake all day long.

00:18:30.630 --> 00:18:33.290 align:middle line:90%
>> Or the all ice cream diet--

00:18:33.290 --> 00:18:36.320 align:middle line:84%
>> OK, so you would lose
weight on that, I'm sure.

00:18:36.320 --> 00:18:39.755 align:middle line:84%
However, again, that's probably
not healthy for long term.

00:18:39.755 --> 00:18:40.880 align:middle line:90%
>> Let's talk about labels.

00:18:40.880 --> 00:18:42.588 align:middle line:84%
I know we're skipping
all over the place.

00:18:42.588 --> 00:18:45.850 align:middle line:84%
There's so much in this book
that people have to learn from.

00:18:45.850 --> 00:18:49.670 align:middle line:84%
>> People need to be good
shoppers and wary consumers.

00:18:49.670 --> 00:18:51.230 align:middle line:84%
And we're lucky
to live at a time

00:18:51.230 --> 00:18:54.310 align:middle line:84%
when food products have to state
their contents on the labels.

00:18:54.310 --> 00:18:56.560 align:middle line:84%
So you want to train yourself
to be a label detective.

00:18:56.560 --> 00:18:59.600 align:middle line:84%
One rule that I follow
is, if they can barely

00:18:59.600 --> 00:19:03.170 align:middle line:84%
fit all the words on the label,
put it back on the shelf.

00:19:03.170 --> 00:19:05.960 align:middle line:84%
If it's something you
would make at home,

00:19:05.960 --> 00:19:08.275 align:middle line:84%
think of what ingredients
you would use to make it.

00:19:08.275 --> 00:19:10.400 align:middle line:84%
And if there's too many
things there that you never

00:19:10.400 --> 00:19:12.330 align:middle line:84%
heard of that you
wouldn't use at home,

00:19:12.330 --> 00:19:13.880 align:middle line:90%
put it back on the shelf.

00:19:13.880 --> 00:19:17.210 align:middle line:84%
If the words, "partially
hydrogenated" anything appear,

00:19:17.210 --> 00:19:18.800 align:middle line:90%
put it back on the shelf.

00:19:18.800 --> 00:19:20.910 align:middle line:84%
Don't buy things with
artificial colors in them.

00:19:20.910 --> 00:19:22.410 align:middle line:90%
These are some simple rules.

00:19:22.410 --> 00:19:24.860 align:middle line:84%
Another one-- there are some
label deceptions out there.

00:19:24.860 --> 00:19:28.250 align:middle line:84%
One of the worst is
the serving size.

00:19:28.250 --> 00:19:30.440 align:middle line:90%
You can buy a bag of chips.

00:19:30.440 --> 00:19:34.400 align:middle line:84%
And I could easily eat half
of that in no time, maybe

00:19:34.400 --> 00:19:37.110 align:middle line:84%
the whole thing, and it gives
you the calories per serving,

00:19:37.110 --> 00:19:39.590 align:middle line:84%
and then you see that there's
12 servings in the bag.

00:19:39.590 --> 00:19:40.680 align:middle line:90%
That's very misleading.

00:19:40.680 --> 00:19:41.460 align:middle line:90%
>> That's two potato chips.

00:19:41.460 --> 00:19:43.627 align:middle line:84%
>> Yeah, very misleading,
so you've got to take that

00:19:43.627 --> 00:19:44.850 align:middle line:90%
into account.

00:19:44.850 --> 00:19:47.540 align:middle line:84%
>> I think that was one of the
most important tips you said

00:19:47.540 --> 00:19:48.423 align:middle line:90%
in your book.

00:19:48.423 --> 00:19:50.840 align:middle line:84%
Because a lot of people say I
can't read that little print

00:19:50.840 --> 00:19:54.500 align:middle line:84%
to look for the words
partially hydrogenated,

00:19:54.500 --> 00:19:56.565 align:middle line:84%
you just say, look
at how long it is.

00:19:56.565 --> 00:19:57.690 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah, that's a good one.

00:19:57.690 --> 00:19:59.398 align:middle line:84%
>> And do that even
without your glasses.

00:19:59.398 --> 00:20:00.320 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes, exactly.

00:20:00.320 --> 00:20:01.528 align:middle line:90%
>> You don't have to read it.

00:20:01.528 --> 00:20:04.220 align:middle line:84%
If it's got a lot of
print, don't buy it.

00:20:04.220 --> 00:20:06.770 align:middle line:90%
>> Don't buy it.

00:20:06.770 --> 00:20:10.220 align:middle line:84%
>> The other tip that was kind
of interesting is you said,

00:20:10.220 --> 00:20:11.910 align:middle line:84%
don't bother going
down the aisles.

00:20:11.910 --> 00:20:14.375 align:middle line:84%
Shopping on the periphery
of the supermarket.

00:20:14.375 --> 00:20:16.850 align:middle line:10%
>> Good Strategy-- in general,
the foods that are around

00:20:16.850 --> 00:20:19.520 align:middle line:10%
the edge of the supermarket,
that's we're going to find

00:20:19.520 --> 00:20:27.260 align:middle line:10%
the produce, for example, the
good quality fish and meats.

00:20:27.260 --> 00:20:29.000 align:middle line:84%
And it's the
interior of the store

00:20:29.000 --> 00:20:31.430 align:middle line:84%
you can find all the
refined and processed foods.

00:20:31.430 --> 00:20:33.350 align:middle line:84%
I think that the
American diet has

00:20:33.350 --> 00:20:35.600 align:middle line:84%
gotten more and more
top heavy and highly

00:20:35.600 --> 00:20:37.700 align:middle line:90%
refined and processed foods.

00:20:37.700 --> 00:20:40.820 align:middle line:84%
I think this is a big factor
in the obesity problem

00:20:40.820 --> 00:20:42.180 align:middle line:90%
that we've got in this country.

00:20:42.180 --> 00:20:44.060 align:middle line:84%
And many of these refined
and processed foods

00:20:44.060 --> 00:20:45.770 align:middle line:84%
are unhealthy for
us in other ways.

00:20:45.770 --> 00:20:47.312 align:middle line:84%
I think that's one
of the things that

00:20:47.312 --> 00:20:49.670 align:middle line:84%
protects people in countries
like France and Italy.

00:20:49.670 --> 00:20:53.060 align:middle line:84%
Even though they're eating foods
that we consider to be rich,

00:20:53.060 --> 00:20:54.920 align:middle line:84%
they're eating smaller
quantities of them,

00:20:54.920 --> 00:20:55.970 align:middle line:90%
and they're not eating all--

00:20:55.970 --> 00:20:57.200 align:middle line:84%
>> Plus they're more
satisfying maybe.

00:20:57.200 --> 00:20:58.560 align:middle line:90%
>> I think so, absolutely.

00:20:58.560 --> 00:21:01.953 align:middle line:84%
And they're not
eating fast food--

00:21:01.953 --> 00:21:04.370 align:middle line:84%
they're going to learn to, but
they're not, at the moment,

00:21:04.370 --> 00:21:06.320 align:middle line:84%
eating fast food
or processed food.

00:21:06.320 --> 00:21:07.580 align:middle line:90%
Here's an interesting story.

00:21:07.580 --> 00:21:09.460 align:middle line:84%
I have known-- I wonder
if you've known this too.

00:21:09.460 --> 00:21:10.918 align:middle line:84%
I've had a number
of friends who've

00:21:10.918 --> 00:21:13.910 align:middle line:84%
gone for vacations in France
and Italy for say a week

00:21:13.910 --> 00:21:16.340 align:middle line:84%
or two who are
concerned about weight

00:21:16.340 --> 00:21:19.320 align:middle line:84%
and just decided they were going
to throw caution to the wind,

00:21:19.320 --> 00:21:20.510 align:middle line:90%
pay no attention.

00:21:20.510 --> 00:21:21.380 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to eat.

00:21:21.380 --> 00:21:24.620 align:middle line:84%
And they insist they got no more
activity than they do at home,

00:21:24.620 --> 00:21:26.720 align:middle line:84%
and they come back
to face the scales,

00:21:26.720 --> 00:21:28.910 align:middle line:84%
and, to their amazement,
they're the same

00:21:28.910 --> 00:21:30.620 align:middle line:84%
or even have lost
a pound or two,

00:21:30.620 --> 00:21:33.020 align:middle line:84%
and they can't
understand what happened.

00:21:33.020 --> 00:21:35.420 align:middle line:84%
I think what happened is
actually they have not

00:21:35.420 --> 00:21:36.350 align:middle line:90%
been eating as much.

00:21:36.350 --> 00:21:38.630 align:middle line:84%
And even though they
think they have,

00:21:38.630 --> 00:21:40.730 align:middle line:84%
the food it's been
so satisfying,

00:21:40.730 --> 00:21:42.520 align:middle line:84%
and you devote all
this attention to it.

00:21:42.520 --> 00:21:44.540 align:middle line:84%
It's not something
you eat on the run.

00:21:44.540 --> 00:21:47.540 align:middle line:84%
It's really a major part
of your day and focus,

00:21:47.540 --> 00:21:49.530 align:middle line:90%
and you're satisfied.

00:21:49.530 --> 00:21:52.050 align:middle line:84%
>> And French people,
I think, do not--

00:21:52.050 --> 00:21:55.340 align:middle line:84%
they go to the fresh
markets to buy vegetables.

00:21:55.340 --> 00:21:57.600 align:middle line:84%
They don't go and get
something off the shelf

00:21:57.600 --> 00:22:02.910 align:middle line:84%
and then throw a
can of onion rings

00:22:02.910 --> 00:22:05.880 align:middle line:84%
in it to mix it up and make--
they put some onion in it.

00:22:05.880 --> 00:22:09.720 align:middle line:84%
>> Right, but, however, it's
very sad to note how quickly

00:22:09.720 --> 00:22:12.540 align:middle line:84%
this is changing all over
the world as a result of us.

00:22:12.540 --> 00:22:14.950 align:middle line:84%
We are exporting American
fast food everywhere

00:22:14.950 --> 00:22:15.750 align:middle line:90%
very successful.

00:22:15.750 --> 00:22:19.390 align:middle line:84%
My editor has a home in
southern France near Provence.

00:22:19.390 --> 00:22:23.220 align:middle line:84%
And he tells me that an American
fast food restaurant opened

00:22:23.220 --> 00:22:25.720 align:middle line:84%
in this region, and it's now
the most popular restaurant

00:22:25.720 --> 00:22:26.520 align:middle line:90%
in the area.

00:22:26.520 --> 00:22:27.210 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, that's too bad.

00:22:27.210 --> 00:22:28.150 align:middle line:90%
>> Sad.

00:22:28.150 --> 00:22:29.940 align:middle line:90%
>> I'm sorry to hear that.

00:22:29.940 --> 00:22:34.080 align:middle line:84%
Well, we've been having a
wonderful time here talking

00:22:34.080 --> 00:22:36.870 align:middle line:84%
to Dr. Andrew Weil,
who is one of the most

00:22:36.870 --> 00:22:40.590 align:middle line:84%
controversial doctors in the
world, about his new book,

00:22:40.590 --> 00:22:42.618 align:middle line:84%
"Eating Well for
Optimum Health."

